sql:
SELECT DISTINCT user_id
FROM processes
WHERE is_critical = 1;

SELECT process_type, AVG(mem_usage) AS avg_mem_usage_kb
FROM processes
GROUP BY process_type;

SELECT image_name, mem_usage
FROM processes
WHERE mem_usage = (SELECT MAX(mem_usage) FROM processes);

SELECT image_name, user_id, mem_usage
FROM processes
WHERE mem_usage = (SELECT MAX(mem_usage) FROM processes);

external_knowledge:
- High memory usage is assumed to be above 50000 KB; 
- Critical processes are those where 'is_critical' equals 1; 
- Memory-intensive processes are those with the highest memory usage.

sql:
